The paper discusses the development of an educational mathematics assistant (EMA) based on Computer Theorem Proving (CTP) and Automated Theorem Proving (ATP). This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of a novel CTP-based programming language, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of the EMA in educational practice, which suggests that it may fall under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Education (cs.EDU).
